SIMPLE: pope
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pope
<hw>Pope</hw> <pr>(p⟦omac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>p⟦amac⟧pa</ets>, L. <ets>papa</ets> father, bishop. Cf.
<er>Papa</er>, <er>Papal</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Any ecclesiastic,
esp. a bishop.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Foxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The bishop of Rome, the head of the Roman Catholic
Church. See <er>Note</er> under <er>Cardinal</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A parish priest, or a chaplain, of the Greek
Church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fish; the ruff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pope Joan</b></col>, <cd>a game at cards played on a
round board with compartments.</cd> -- <col><b>Pope's eye</b></col>,
<cd>the gland surrounded with fat in the middle of the thigh of an ox or
sheep.</cd> <au>R. D. Blackmore.</au> -- <col><b>Pope's nose</b></col>,
<cd>the rump, or uropygium, of a bird. See <er>Uropygium</er>.</cd> --
<col><b>to be more Catholic than the Pope</b></col> <cd>to adhere more
stringently to Roman Catholic practices and doctrine than is required by
church doctrine; -- usually used in a negative sense to mean, to be
excessively pious.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Popedom</ent>⟦br⟧
